result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Sirae Annie Kettula

records.addlTxt: Letter RE: restitution
Deferred agreement- extended

11:52 AM Defendant, Sirae Annie Kettula, appeared.  Atty. Daniel Patrick Steffen appeared on behalf of State of Wisconsin.  Def by phone.  Court reviews, def under DJOC with the State, restitution is part of DJOC, def behind on restitution payments- still owes over $5000 and wants to extend the DJOC to allow more time to pay restitution.  Court asks for financial/employment information from def, def provides.  State wants to extend the agreement for 2 years.  Court asks if def agrees to extend for 2 years; def does.  State to amend DJOC to include making $250 monthly payments on restitution.  Court grants the extension- agreement will be amended and modified to include the extension and include the monthly payment amount.  DA Steffen to mail amended agreement to def, def to sign and return as quickly as possible, and the agreement will be entered as an order.

Defendant, Sirae Annie Kettula, appeared with Attorney James McLaughlin.  Attorney Joseph M. Schieffer appeared for the State.  Atty McLaughlin addresses the Court, DJOC 24 months because of > $6,000 restitution,  jt and several w/Justin Ladd. The Court examines Def. re: the DJOC. She understands the charges and rights she is pleading to and waiving. She believes the State has enough proof to find her guilty beyond a reasonable doubt, and the Court could sentence her to the Max.  and 15CF206 will be DRI, explained to the Def. No threats or promises made to her to plead today. She admits the facts are accurate in the PC statement. She wishes to move forward. As to Count 1 in 15CF112 Def. enters G plea KIV, the Court finds a FB for a plea. She fully understands the agreement and the Restitution needs to be paid in full by her. The State argues for approval of the DJOC. Certificate of Victim compliance filed by the State. Atty McLaughlin readdresses the Court. Def enters aloq. The Court adopts the DJOC.
